<subSubSection id="C37A65197128FFF6D9940A05FBCC0316" pageId="1" pageNumber="486" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDF36927128FFF6D9940A05FE740375" blockId="1.[174,1233,1387,1606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">
Diagnosis. The species is characterized by the smooth face; relatively wide, moreor-less flat yellow clypeus; complete occipital carina; smooth mesoscutum; fore wing with vein 3 
<emphasis id="B914EA807128FFF6D98E0AC2FE9E0095" box="[249,303,1452,1477]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">rs-m</emphasis>
absent; propodeum with strong lateromedian longitudinal carinae reaching well defined area apicalis; orange hind tibiae; granulate metasomal tergites 1–2; weakly upcurved female ovipositor, about 1.8–2.0 times as long as the hind tibia length; male antenna lacking tyloids.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF36927128FFF6D9940942FBCC0316" blockId="1.[174,1233,1387,1606]" box="[227,1149,1579,1606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="486">
